The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Party backs Zardari for PM: Paper
                                                                                                               Party backs Zardari for PM: Paper
                            
	Islamabad, March 12 (PTI): The Pakistan Peoples Party (PPP) has decided in principle to nominate co-chairman Asif Ali Zardari for the Prime Ministers post, the Daily Times paper said.        
	However, he will be eligible to occupy the post only after being elected to the National Assembly.        
	The PPP, which is the single-largest party in the House, is offering Makhdoom Amin Fahim, till recently the frontrunner for the Prime Ministers post, the position of parliamentary leader in the National Assembly.         
	The party is also offering his son the post of adviser to the PM with the status of a federal minister, the Daily Times said.        
	Zardari has assigned a senior party leader to convey this offer to Amin Fahim and return with a response soon, the Daily Times said quoting a source who is close to Zardari.                                                                                                                                                                                     
